# Lesson 1.1

# What Memecoins Really Are

## Core Idea

Memecoins are **attention markets**.

Not technology.

Not fundamentals.

Not utility.

Memecoins move because **people talk about them**.

More attention → more buyers → higher price.

Simple.

Your guide explains that memecoins are essentially **psychological experiments wrapped in memes**. 

---

## The 4 Drivers of Memecoin Value

A memecoin pumps when it has these elements.

### 1 — Community

Strong communities create belief.

10,000 believers will outperform a technically superior coin.

People buy because **others believe**.

---

### 2 — Viral Potential

If a meme spreads easily, the coin spreads easily.

Ask:

Can someone explain the meme in **one sentence**?

Example:

Dog coin
Gigachad coin
AI meme coin

Simple = viral.

---

### 3 — Emotional Reaction

Memecoins trigger emotions.

They make people:

• laugh
• feel part of a tribe
• feel early
• feel lucky

Emotion creates buying pressure.

---

### 4 — Accessibility

Anyone must be able to buy it easily.

If a teenager with $10 can buy it on their phone → good.

Low friction = more buyers.

---

## The Mental Model

Memecoins are not investing.

They are **surfing waves of human attention**. 

Imagine:

Attention = ocean waves

Traders = surfers

The earlier you catch the wave, the bigger the ride.

---

